Panera Bread has a nice variety of fairly healthy eating choices. Their menu changes a couple of times per year, so don't get used to one item. If you order a drink, you can select from an assortment of pastries for 99 cents. Atmosphere is pleasant and not too loud or noisy. The floor and interior surfaces were clean and well kept. The last time I was there some of the seat cushions were ripped or torn making the restaurant look older than it is. I have been there several times and I find the staff I interacted with to be very polite and friendly. At times, it does get crowded, but I have not had any issues finding a place to sit. They also offer outdoor seating on the Veterans side with umbrellas for shade. Seats along the wall had outlets for phone chargers and they do offer free wifi. Panera Bread serves Pepsi products with 3 or 4 flavored tea combinations with a self service drink machine. Bathrooms were clean and free of trash. The rewards system for frequent guests is not easy to understand. Of the several times I have used my rewards card, I have not received anything, so I am not sure how many times you need to go or what you do get for a reward.
